  },
  {
    q: "Can I get an engagement ring for under CA$1,000 in Canada?",
    a: "Yes. A moissanite stone in a 0.75&ndash;1ct equivalent size with a standard 14K solitaire setting is achievable in this budget. Lab-grown diamonds at 0.5ct are also possible. The <a href='https://luxjewels.com/booking-appointment/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>free consultation</a> or <a href='https://stan.store/luxjewels' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>No-BS Call</a> will map exactly what's achievable at your number."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between lab-grown diamonds and moissanite?",
    a: "Lab-grown diamonds are diamonds. Moissanite is silicon carbide, a completely different material with a higher refractive index (more rainbow fire), slightly lower hardness at 9.25 vs 10, and a significantly lower price point. Both are durable enough for everyday wear on an engagement ring."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you offer custom ring design?",
    a: "Yes. About 60% of rings built at Lux Jewels are fully custom from the first conversation. The process starts with a free 30&ndash;40 minute video consultation, moves through CAD rendering and approval, then stone sourcing with an IGI report before you commit. <a href='/custom-engagement-rings/'>Learn more about custom design.</a>"
  },
  {
    q: "Do you ship across Canada?",
    a: "Yes. Lux Jewels ships to all Canadian provinces via FedEx Priority, insured with signature required. Typical delivery is next-day once shipped. We also ship to the US."
  },
  {
